[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---README---[39m                                                                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m# Relay Agent Assistant[39m                                                         [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mShared open-source assistant SDK/runtime for AgentWorkforce products such as [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mSage, MSD, NightCTO, and future assistants.[39m                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## What This Repo Is[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThis repository defines the shared assistant layer that sits above Relay [39m       [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mfoundation infrastructure and below product-specific assistants.[39m                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mIt exists to centralize assistant concerns that should not be reimplemented in [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mevery product:[39m                                                                  [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- assistant identity and runtime composition[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- memory contracts and shared retrieval/persistence patterns[39m                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- session continuity across surfaces[39m                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- proactive behavior and scheduled follow-up engines[39m                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- multi-agent coordination behind one assistant identity[39m                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- policy, approvals, and audit hooks[39m                                            [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThis repo is intentionally docs-first. It establishes package boundaries, [39m      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231madoption guidance, and extraction order before implementation code is [39m          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mintroduced.[39m                                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mConnectivity is one of the sharper early package candidates because internal [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231massistant communication needs stronger rules than generic chatter. The package [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mspike is documented here:[39m                                                       [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- [Connectivity package README](packages/connectivity/README.md)[39m                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- [Connectivity package spec](docs/architecture/connectivity-package-spec.md)[39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- [Connectivity adoption guide](docs/consumer/connectivity-adoption-guide.md)[39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- [Connectivity patterns research](docs/research/connectivity-patterns.md)[39m      [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## What Consumers Should Expect[39m                                                 [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mProducts should eventually import focused SDK packages from this repo, for [39m     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mexample:[39m                                                                        [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `@relay-assistant/core`[39m                                                       [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `@relay-assistant/memory`[39m                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `@relay-assistant/proactive`[39m                                                  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- [39m                                                                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m… +1464 lines …[39m                                                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231ment the SDK in narrow slices[39m                                                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m6. Keep the goal explicit: Sage, MSD, and NightCTO should be able to begin [39m     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mconsuming the exportable SDK by the end of the weekend[39m                          [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mEnd the document with SPEC_PROGRAM_PLAN_READY.[39m                                  [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mSTEP OWNER CONTRACT:[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- You are the accountable owner for step "lead-plan".[39m                           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- If you delegate, you must still verify completion yourself.[39m                   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Preferred final decision format:[39m                                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  OWNER_DECISION: <one of COMPLETE, INCOMPLETE_RETRY, INCOMPLETE_FAIL, [39m         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mNEEDS_CLARIFICATION>[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  REASON: <one sentence>[39m                                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Legacy completion marker still supported: STEP_COMPLETE:lead-plan[39m             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Then self-terminate immediately with /exit.[39m                                   [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mAUTONOMOUS DELEGATION — READ THIS BEFORE STARTING:[39m                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mYou have approximately 60 minutes before this step times out. Plan accordingly [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m— delegate early if the work is substantial.[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mBefore diving in, assess whether this task is too large or complex for a single[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m agent. If it involves multiple independent subtasks, touches many files, or [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mcould take a long time, you should break it down and delegate to helper agents [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mto avoid timeouts.[39m                                                              [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mOption 1 — Spawn relay agents (for real parallel coding work):[39m                  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - mcp__relaycast__agent_add(name="helper-1", cli="claude", task="Specific [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231msubtask description")[39m                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Coordinate via mcp__relaycast__message_dm_send(to="helper-1", text="...")[39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Check on them with mcp__relaycast__message_inbox_check()[39m                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Clean up when done: mcp__relaycast__agent_remove(name="helper-1")[39m           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mOption 2 — Use built-in sub-agents (Task tool) for research or scoped work:[39m     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Good for exploring code, reading files, or making targeted changes[39m          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Can run multiple sub-agents in parallel[39m                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mGuidelines:[39m                                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- You are the lead — delegate but stay in control, track progress, integrate [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mresults[39m                                                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Give each helper a clear, self-contained task with enough context to work [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mindependently[39m                                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- For simple or quick work, just do it yourself — don't over-delegate[39m           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Always release spawned relay agents when their work is complete[39m               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- When spawning non-claude agents (codex, gemini, etc.), prepend to their task:[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  "RELAY SETUP: First call register(name='<exact-agent-name>') before any other[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m relay tool."[39m                                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mIMPORTANT: When you have fully completed this task, you MUST self-terminate by [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231meither: (a) calling remove_agent(name: "<your-agent-name>", reason: "task [39m      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mcompleted") — preferred, or (b) outputting the exact text "/exit" on its own [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mline as a fallback. Do not wait for further input — terminate immediately after[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m finishing. Do NOT spawn sub-agents unless the task explicitly requires it.[39m     [49m

